TY  - JOUR
T1  - When Mindsets Collide: Switching Analytical Mindsets to Advance Organization Science
AU  - Zyphur, Michael J.
Y1  - 2009/10/01
PY  - 2009
DA  - 2009/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.34.4.zok677
DO  - 10.5465/amr.34.4.zok677
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 677
EP  - 688
VL  - 34
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Analytic techniques have associated mindsets that can determine the way scholars conceptualize their objects of study. I propose that switching these ?analytical mindsets? can lead to new theoretical insights. Using two examples, I show how switching analytical mindsets allows for divergent, creative thinking that can help researchers generate new theoretical foci. I conclude by discussing the importance of attending to methodology when engaging in the process of theory construction.
AB  - Analytic techniques have associated mindsets that can determine the way scholars conceptualize their objects of study. I propose that switching these ?analytical mindsets? can lead to new theoretical insights. Using two examples, I show how switching analytical mindsets allows for divergent, creative thinking that can help researchers generate new theoretical foci. I conclude by discussing the importance of attending to methodology when engaging in the process of theory construction.
