TY  - JOUR
T1  - Organizational Path Dependence: Opening the Black Box
AU  - Sydow, Jörg
AU  - Schreyögg, Georg
AU  - Koch, Jochen
Y1  - 2009/10/01
PY  - 2009
DA  - 2009/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.34.4.zok689
DO  - 10.5465/amr.34.4.zok689
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 689
EP  - 709
VL  - 34
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - To enable a better understanding of the underlying logic of path dependence, we set forth a theoretical framework explaining how organizations become path dependent. At its core are the dynamics of self-reinforcing mechanisms, which are likely to lead an organization into a lock-in. By drawing on studies of technological paths, we conceptualize the emergent process of path dependence along three distinct stages. We also use the model to explore breakouts from organizational path dependence and discuss implications for managing and researching organizational paths.
AB  - To enable a better understanding of the underlying logic of path dependence, we set forth a theoretical framework explaining how organizations become path dependent. At its core are the dynamics of self-reinforcing mechanisms, which are likely to lead an organization into a lock-in. By drawing on studies of technological paths, we conceptualize the emergent process of path dependence along three distinct stages. We also use the model to explore breakouts from organizational path dependence and discuss implications for managing and researching organizational paths.
