TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Organization of Regional Clusters
AU  - Bell, Simon J.
AU  - Tracey, Paul
AU  - Heide, Jan B.
Y1  - 2009/10/01
PY  - 2009
DA  - 2009/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.34.4.zok623
DO  - 10.5465/amr.34.4.zok623
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 623
EP  - 642
VL  - 34
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We introduce a model of interorganizational governance within regional clusters. Drawing on the ?new institutional economics? literature, we show how firms' governance designs are shaped by the relationship between transaction-level characteristics and the cluster macroculture. We then consider how subsequent transaction-level governance designs are affected by path dependencies from past governance choices. Finally, we suggest that intertransactional path dependencies exhibit directional asymmetries, and we draw implications for the literature on clusters, on transaction costs, and on interorganizational relationships.
AB  - We introduce a model of interorganizational governance within regional clusters. Drawing on the ?new institutional economics? literature, we show how firms' governance designs are shaped by the relationship between transaction-level characteristics and the cluster macroculture. We then consider how subsequent transaction-level governance designs are affected by path dependencies from past governance choices. Finally, we suggest that intertransactional path dependencies exhibit directional asymmetries, and we draw implications for the literature on clusters, on transaction costs, and on interorganizational relationships.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.34.4.zok623
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.34.4.zok623
